dct_title_s: Greater Germany, major administrative divisions, 1 July, 1944 / lithographed in the Reproduction Branch, OSS.
dct_description_sm: No relief shown. Map shows Germany Reich and pre-war 1937 international borders, Reichsgau, General-Gouverment, Protektorat, Regierungsbezirk, Distrikt and Kreis, Stadtkreis administrative boundaries. Administrative boundaries are color coded and indexed. Map shows the boundaries established by the Greater Reich covering: Germany Austria, Leichstein, French Alsace-Lorraine area, Poland, Czechoslovakia, and Lithuania. Includes location map, "Reliability of data" table, and notes. "FREE"--In upper right border and center lower border In lower left margin: "No. 5408 -- R & A, OSS, rev. 1 May, 1945."
dct_creator_sm: United States. Office of Strategic Services. Research and Analysis Branch
dct_publisher_sm: [Washington, D.C.] : Research & Analysis, Office of Strategic Services, 1945.
